sub_title: Communication advisor | I help social organisations with human communication
summary:
Since childhood, I have been involved in design, communication and storytelling. So it was no surprise that I decided to study communication. However, I wanted to challenge myself by following this study at an international school. As a result, I was able to study and work in South Korea, England and Germany in addition to be active in an international setting in the Netherlands.

Because I got to know so many different cultures and people, I really started to realise the power of a story. It is something that is the same in every culture: how we learn to understand each other, create deep connections and shape our lives.

When I decided to go on an adventure in 2020 and move to Japan for a year, I seized the opportunity to combine the theoretical and creative side of communication and to spend the whole day telling stories. I also wanted to do create something that could make the world a little bit better. From this mix, √âclaire Studio was born. 

Unfortunately, covid-19 cancelled my travel plans and thus I stil am in the beautiful Netherlands, but now I get to enjoy working with passionate entrepreneurs every day!
